    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 26-SI SERIES - REPAIR PROCEDURES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl0801803">
        <title>REPAIR PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
            <para>After removing the cover plate, cover and gasket, the rectifier end frame components are exposed to
                view as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801807">Figure 6</hotlnk>. Note carefully the proper connections, then proceed as
                follows:
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801807" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801806" filename="../figg08/G0801806.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>End View, Cover Removed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. "R" TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REGULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. INSULATED REGULATOR MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. OUTPUT TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. RECTIFIER BRIDGE TERMINAL NUTS (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. DIODE TRIO AND CAPACITOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. DIODE (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. FIELD LEADS</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. CAPACITOR GROUND AND DIODE MOUNTING TAB</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. CAPACITOR LEAD CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To check the stator and diodes, remove three regulator leads, three rectifier bridge
                    nuts and leads, six diode leads and the "R" terminal lead from the three studs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To check the field coil, disconnect the two field coil leads from the regulator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Later on, it may be necessary to separate the drive end frame assembly from the
                    rectifier end frame assembly by removing the shaft nut, washer, pulley, baffle, fan, slinger and
                    thru bolts from the drive end.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
